  <text>
    <body>
      <ab type="lido:objectWorkType">Photograph</ab>
      <ab subtype="creation" type="lido:event">
        <date>1928</date>
      </ab>
      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">The photograph shows hand-painted advertising for the feature film ‘Živi leš’ (Living corpse) on a white poster displayed on a building and written in Serbian Cyrillic. In the forefront, a man is standing and another is seated. Photographs are displayed to their right and left</ab>
      <ab subtype="comment" type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">The original name of the film with the Serbo-Croatian title ‘Živi leš’, which must have been released before 1928, cannot be identified. The two men in the centre of the picture are possibly employees of a photo studio. Vrnjačka Banja is a spa in Serbia.</ab>
